val2 is bitwise OR of val1 and val2.\nval1 & val2 is bitwise AND of val1 and val2.\n\n \nExample 1:\n\nInput: nums = [1,4]\nOutput: 5\nExplanation: \nThe triplets and their corresponding effective values are listed below:\n- (0,0,0) with effective value ((1 | 1) & 1) = 1\n- (0,0,1) with effective value ((1 | 1) & 4) = 0\n- (0,1,0) with effective value ((1 | 4) & 1) = 1\n- (0,1,1) with effective value ((1 | 4) & 4) = 4\n- (1,0,0) with effective value ((4 | 1) & 1) = 1\n- (1,0,1) with effective value ((4 | 1) & 4) = 4\n- (1,1,0) with effective value ((4 | 4) & 1) = 0\n- (1,1,1) with effective value ((4 | 4) & 4) = 4 \nXor-beauty of array will be bitwise XOR of all beauties = 1 ^ 0 ^ 1 ^ 4 ^ 1 ^ 4 ^ 0 ^ 4 = 5.\nExample 2:\n\nInput: nums = [15,45,20,2,34,35,5,44,32,30]\nOutput: 34\nExplanation: The xor-beauty of the given array is 34.\n\n \nConstraints:\n\n1 <= nums.length <= 105\n1 <= nums[i] <= 109\n\n\n\n### Format: You will use the following starter code to write the solution to the problem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def xorBeauty(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "To solve this problem, we need to compute the XOR beauty of the array as defined. The effective value of three indices \\(i\\), \\(j\\), and \\(k\\) is given by \\(((\\text{nums}[i] \\, | \\, \\text{nums}[j]) \\, \\& \\, \\text{nums}[k])\\). The XOR beauty is the XOR of all such effective values for every possible triplet \\((i, j, k)\\).\n\nGiven the constraints, a brute-force approach that calculates the effective value for every triplet would be computationally expensive (O(n^3)), so we need a more efficient solution.\n\n### Key Insight:\nThe problem can be simplified using properties of XOR and bitwise operations. By carefully analyzing the expression, it turns out that the XOR beauty of the array is simply the XOR of all elements in the array. This can be derived from the properties of XOR and the symmetry in the expression.\n\nHere's the Python code to solve the problem efficiently:\n\n```python\nfrom typing import List\n\nclass Solution:\n    def xorBeauty(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        result = 0\n        for num in nums:\n            result ^= num\n        return result\n```\n\n### Explanation:\n1. We initialize `result` to 0.\n2. We iterate through each number in the array `nums`.\n3. For each number, we XOR it with `result`.\n4. After processing all numbers, `result` will hold the XOR beauty of the array.\n\nThis solution runs in O(n) time complexity, which is efficient given the constraints.", "estimated_date": 1672531200000}